            <fr:title text="weak factorization system">weak factorization system</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Given two classes of maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}, \mathcal {R}]]></fr:tex> in a category, it is a <html:strong>weak factorization system</html:strong> if every morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> factorizes as <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[X \xrightarrow {\mathcal {L}} Z \xrightarrow {\mathcal {R}} Y,]]></fr:tex> and a morphism belongs to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}]]></fr:tex> iff it left lifts against every morphism in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {R}]]></fr:tex>, and vice versa.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
